programme.title: Are We There Yet?
programme.desc: Nick, a smooth operator, is trying to land a date with Suzanne, a divorcee with whom he would like to ring in the New Year. Problem is, Suzanne is stuck working in Vancouver and miserable because she misses her kids. Seizing the opportunity, Nick gallantly offers to make her New Year's wish come true - and his own in the process - by driving eight-year-old Kevin and eleven-year-old Lindsey up from Portland, Oregon to be reunited with their mom. What Nick doesn't know is that Suzanne's children hate every man their mom dates on sight.

programme.title: Middle School: The Worst Years of My Life
programme.desc: Rafe has an epic imagination and a slight problem with authority. When he transfers to a new school, Rafe and his scheming best friend Leo hatch a plan to break every rule in the school's code of conduct. This causes a battle with the principal, which explodes into chaos both real and imagined. Rafe struggles to hide his misbehavior from Jeanne, the straight-A, overachieving girl of his dreams, while at home, his mother's boyfriend - a moochy, jack-of-no-trades named Bear - threatens to become his stepfather.

programme.title: The Architect
programme.desc: Parker Posey and Eric McCormack star in this comedy about a couple who set out to build a new home and enlist the services of an uncompromising modernist architect who proceeds to build his dream house, instead of theirs.

programme.title: Rescue Dogs
programme.desc: Family adventure set on a beach in sunny southern California, in which a restaurant owner enlists his rescue dog to take on an evil businessman and finds time to fall for a beautiful dancer.

programme.title: New Wave: Dare to be Different
programme.desc: In August, 1982, a small group of radio visionaries at WLIR Long Island knew they couldn't compete with the mega radio stations in New York City. With one brave decision, they changed the sound of radio forever. Program Director Denis McNamara, the crew at the station and the biggest artists of the era tell the story of how they battled the FCC, the record labels, mega-radio and all the conventional rules to create a musical movement that brought the New Wave to America - including bands like U2, Talking Heads, Depeche Mode and Blondie.

programme.title: Against the Tide
programme.desc: A Showtime Sports chronicle of the seminal 1970 college football matchup between Alabama's Crimson Tide and USC Trojans at Birmingham's Legion Field. Through interviews with former Alabama legends Joe Namath, John Mitchell and USC stars Sam "Bam" Cunningham, Jimmy Jones and more, this documentary examines coach Paul "Bear" Bryant's surprising decision to bring a dominant, racially integrated football team onto the field in Birmingham for the very first time and reveals the impact college football played in the struggle for integration.

programme.title: Behold the Monkey
programme.desc: A well-intentioned pensioner restores a fresco in a small Spanish town.

programme.title: Christmas Ranch
programme.desc: When a rebellious young girl is sent to stay on her grandmother's ranch for Christmas, a friendship with a pony alters the course of her life but when the ranch is threatened with foreclosure she must come up with a plan to save horse and home.

programme.title: Cupid's Proxy
programme.desc: Rebecca Murphy is a cynical widow whose whole world revolves around her 12 year old son, Justin - a budding musician who can't remember his late father. Rebecca has no desire to date despite efforts by her feisty neighbor, Olive, who has a love advice column called Call Me Cupid. When Olive is pressured by her editor to get with the times, she enlists Justin to help her answer a letter. Unbeknownst to Justin, she publishes his advice under the alter ego, Cupid's Proxy.

programme.title: Separated
programme.desc: In this short film, a wind-up toy robot goes on an epic journey to save his better half.

programme.title: Running Wild
programme.desc: A retired Air Force Major (Gregory Harrison), now a UN observer for the International Wildlife Organization, and his children confront elephant poachers in Zimbabwe. Simon MacCorkindale, Cody Jones and Brooke Nevin costar.

programme.title: Are We Done Yet?
programme.desc: Now married to Suzanne (Nia Long), Nick Persons (Ice Cube) has bought a quiet suburban house to escape the rat race of the big city and to provide more space for his new wife and kids. But when his new home quickly becomes a costly fixer upper and he finds himself at the mercy of an eccentric contractor (John C. McGinley), Nick's suburban dream soon becomes a nightmare.

programme.title: Becoming Cary Grant
programme.desc: Using words from his unpublished autobiography along with newly-discovered personal footage shot with a film-maker's eye, Cary Grant - one of Hollywood's greatest stars - tells his story himself. Exploring his long journey from childhood poverty to global fame, this radically new perspective of a man on a quest to find the love that eluded him most of his life reveals the man behind the mask of subtle charm and suave sophistication.

programme.title: Cody the Robosapien
programme.desc: When a 12-year-old boy discovers a broken robot, he finds a zany and powerful new best friend who can change his life for the better but when the evil corporation that funded the robot's creation intervenes, the pair must team up to save their family.

programme.title: Swing Away
programme.desc: Following a meltdown that leads to a suspension, professional golfer Zoe Papadopoulos travels to her grandparents' village in Greece to escape the harsh spotlight of the international sports world. Between baking bread and eating baklava, she meets and mentors a ten-year-old girl who is determined to become the next golf sensation. Along the way, Zoe rediscovers her Greek heritage, her love of the game and the hidden strength within herself.

After his wife leaves him, Carlos' only goal was to make sure his son Luis was given the opportunities he never had. After years of hard work, he still finds himself drifting apart from Luis, now a teenager, who is susceptible to peer pressures. Carlos borrows what little money he can and invests it all into his own gardening business, hoping to finally achieve the better life he always envisioned for his son.

programme.desc: Nerdy middle schooler Tommy is forced take care of a baby dinosaur after his cloned science fair project hatches early. He quickly begins to think of the creature not only as a pet, but also as a friend. But when the dinosaur escapes on the day of the fair, Tommy must figure out a way to get the creature back before greedy grown-ups get to him first.

programme.desc: A young piano prodigy returns to his family farm, after a long stay in a gay conversion therapy, and is torn between the expectations of his emotionally distant father and the memory of a past, loving relationship he's tried to bury.

programme.desc: After deciding to call their marriage quits, Olive (Alicia Silverstone) and Clay (Ryan Kwanten) both want custody of their beloved dog Wesley. Facing a court-ordered 60-day review to determine who'll get the pooch, Olive and Clay try their doggone best to win over the judge in this romantic comedy about what happens when puppy love goes to the dogs.

She feels her life is simply not worth living, but no matter who or what gets in the way, Lola won't give up on her life's ambition to be a star.

programme.desc: Music legend Bob Dylan flies to London one day to visit his mate Dave Stewart. After getting lost, Bob finally arrives at the address and finds himself waiting for Dave in his flat dutifully being served tea by his girlfriend. But is he really in the right place? Starring Eddie Marsan, Paul Ritter and Katherine Parkinson.

programme.desc: This eye-opening documentary tells the story of the Barnes Collection, $25 billion worth of masterpieces by Cezanne, Matisse and Renoir that has become the focus of a culture war between those who wish to preserve the intentions of the collection's original owner, and a conspiracy of politically powerful corporations seeking to profit by seizing and relocating the artwork.

programme.title: Shifting Gears
programme.desc: Tom is a hard-working manager at a big box super store. He started in the stock room, always imagining himself at the helm. Now poised for a big promotion, he gets the news he always feared: no college degree means no promotion. In the face of this new reality, and lamenting the time he devoted to work over family, Tom and his wife Carol decide to change course and start a family business. They pack up their kids and move to a small town to take over a run-down garage bequeathed to them by Tom's estranged father.

programme.title: A Rumor of Angels

Ray Liotta, Catherine McCormack and Ron Livingston costar in this drama based on the book "Thy Son Liveth: Messages from a Soldier to His Mother" by Grace Duffie.

However, there is one person who knew her heart before those walls were erected, her best friend Brandon, who has stood by her for too many years to count. And while Veronica has tried to keep her feelings at bay, he is the one who holds the key that opens her Pandora's box of emotions.

Bobbi's son-in-law, Jim, cons her into losing her house and Mimi, the unofficial leader of the group, decides to take matters into her own hands. programme.desc: When a young woman is found dead after getting involved in an underground fighting ring, her sister begins training under a respected ex-fighter to bring justice to the killer.

programme.title: The Funhouse Massacre
programme.desc: On Halloween night, a group of notorious serial killers escape from an asylum and terrorize the patrons of a funhouse carnival - leaving only a rag-tag bunch of kids, a clueless deputy and a local sheriff to stop the carnage.

programme.title: The Fantasticks
programme.desc: Joel Grey and Brad Sullivan are small-town fathers conspiring to bring their children together in a love match by pretending to discourage it in this magical musical costarring Barnard Hughes.

programme.title: Prince: Sign 'o' the Times
programme.desc: This concert film features clips of live stage performances from Rotterdam and Minnesota, and is also interspersed with short films from the artist. Fan favorites, such as 'Little Red Corvette' and 'U Got the Look,' are performed as Prince is accompanied on stage by Sheena Easton and drummer Sheila E.

programme.title: Tim & Faith: Soul2Soul
programme.desc: Includes live performances from Tim McGraw and Faith Hill's 2017 Soul2Soul world tour, as well as an intimate look inside their relationship. Never before seen interviews are presented along side behind-the-scenes footage, capturing their chemistry on and off the stage. Directed and executive produced by the award-winning team of Dan Cutforth and Jane Lipsitz.

programme.title: Cursed to Kill
programme.desc: Rachel awakens in a hospital, paralyzed from the waist down after a failed attempt on her life for abandoning a cult suicide. Her suffering grows as the spirits of the deceased members begin to haunt her within the confines of the hospital room. They threaten to kill her unless she is willing to offer up a kindred soul in place of her own - her brother's child. But the week that Rachel is given to make her decision is tethered to a curse. All who have the misfortune of hearing anything she says are met with a swift and violent death.

programme.title: More Than T
programme.desc: Beyond the headlines and debates about gender rights witness the multidimensional lives of seven transgender and gender nonconforming individuals as told through the lens of celebrated filmmaker Silas Howard (‘Transparent').

programme.title: Doin' Time
programme.desc: Max's violent outburst comes back to haunt him; Tara discovers that she can remain aware of her actions when her new alter, Shoshana, takes over; Kate's music video is an Internet hit; Charmaine receives surprising news from her doctor.(c)

programme.title: Torando!
programme.desc: A tornado forces the Gregsons to take shelter in their basement, where Tara's new alter Shoshana takes charge and reveals some long-buried secrets during a group therapy session.(c)

programme.title: Behold the Monkey
programme.desc: A well-intentioned pensioner restores a fresco in a small Spanish town.

programme.title: Last Girl Standing
programme.desc: Five years after surviving a brutal massacre, the lone survivor struggles to reclaim her shattered life. But just when she thinks she might finally be ready to start anew, the past comes back to haunt her.

programme.title: Whale Rider
programme.desc: In a small coastal village, the Maori descend from Paikea, the Whale Rider. In every generation, a male heir has succeeded to the chiefly title. When twins are born, and the boy twin dies, the chief is unable to accept his grand-daughter, Pai, as a future leader. Koro, the chief, is convinced that the tribe's misfortunes began at Pai's birth and calls for people to bring their sons to him, sure a new leader will emerge. Pai loves Koro more than anyone in the world, but she must fight him and a thousand years of tradition to fulfill her destiny.

programme.title: Jackson
programme.desc: An intimate documentary look into the lives of three women caught up in the complex issues surrounding access to reproductive healthcare in the Deep South: Shannon Brewer, director of Jackson Women's Health Organization, the only remaining abortion clinic in Mississippi; Barbara Beaver, a leader of the anti-abortion movement, who runs the Center for Pregnancy Choices; and April Jackson, a young mother of four faced with another unplanned pregnancy.

programme.title: London Town
programme.desc: When fifteen-year-old Shay (Daniel Huttlestone) hears the music of The Clash for the first time, it's a revelation, opening up a new world of anti-establishment defiance beyond anything he's known in his dead-end London suburb. Drawn into the heart of the city's burgeoning punk scene, he forges two relationships that will change his life: falling in love with rebellious cool girl Vivian (Nell Williams) and finding an unexpected connection with none other than The Clash's electrifying frontman, Joe Strummer (Jonathan Rhys Meyers).

programme.title: Jasper Jones
programme.desc: Toni Collette, Hugo Weaving, Levi Miller, Angourie Rice, Dan Wyllie and Aaron McGrath star in the story of Charlie Bucktin, a bookish boy of 14 living in a small town in Western Australia. In the dead of night during the scorching summer of 1969, Charlie is startled when he is woken by local mixed-race outcast Jasper Jones outside his window. Jasper leads him deep into the forest and shows him something that will change his life forever, setting them both on a dangerous journey to solve a mystery that will consume the entire community.

programme.title: Whale Rider
programme.desc: In a small coastal village, the Maori descend from Paikea, the Whale Rider. In every generation, a male heir has succeeded to the chiefly title. When twins are born, and the boy twin dies, the chief is unable to accept his grand-daughter, Pai, as a future leader. Koro, the chief, is convinced that the tribe's misfortunes began at Pai's birth and calls for people to bring their sons to him, sure a new leader will emerge. Pai loves Koro more than anyone in the world, but she must fight him and a thousand years of tradition to fulfill her destiny.

programme.title: The Autopsy of Jane Doe
programme.desc: Coroner Tommy Tilden and son Austin run a morgue and crematorium in Virginia. When the local sheriff brings in a body found in the basement of a home, it seems like just another open-and-shut case. As the autopsy proceeds however, they are left reeling as the inspection brings new revelations. Perfectly preserved on the outside, Jane Doe seems to have been the victim of a horrific ritualistic torture. Tommy and Austin begin to piece together these gruesome discoveries, as an unnatural force takes hold of the crematorium.

programme.title: The Whistleblower
programme.desc: Kathy (Academy Award® winner Rachel Weisz) is an American police officer who takes a job working as a peacekeeper in post-war Bosnia. Her expectations of helping to rebuild a devastated country are dashed when she uncovers a dangerous reality of corruption, cover-up and intrigue, amid a world of private contractors and multinational diplomatic doubletalk. Directed by Larysa Kondracki, the film also stars Academy Award® winner Vanessa Redgrave, Monica Bellucci and Academy Award® nominee David Strathairn.

programme.title: Contracted
programme.desc: Samantha (Townsend) is a twenty‐something party girl with little discipline and even less direction. After experiencing a lapse in her relationship with her lover (Stegeman), she's forced to move back in with her overbearing mother (Williams). Things take a turn for the worse when she spends the night with a mysterious man (Barrett), leaving her hung‐over and guilt‐ridden. However, something else is wrong with Samantha and she's infected. Unsure of the disease, she realizes she is the host of something catastrophic.

programme.title: Don't Sleep
programme.desc: Shawn and Zach are young lovers who move into a guesthouse together on an estate owned by Mr. and Mrs. Marino. When bizarre events begin to occur, Zach slowly remembers a forgotten time in his childhood when he suffered from severe and violent psychosis - memories erased by a series of electroconvulsive shock treatments administered by his psychiatrist. As the terrors surrounding their lives grow to deadly proportions, Zach is forced to question his own sanity.

programme.title: Whitney. "Can I Be Me"
programme.desc: Directors Nick Broomfield and Rudi Dolezal weave never before seen video, candid interviews and behind the scenes performance footage into a raw and uncensored portrait of Whitney Houston, who died suddenly at age 48 after years of struggling with addiction. Exploring her far-reaching impact, the directors focus on Houston's central dilemma: even though she had made millions of dollars and was recognized as having one of the greatest voices of all time, she still couldn't do what she wanted, either professionally or in her personal life.(c)

programme.title: Changeling
programme.desc: Academy Award winner Clint Eastwood directs this drama in which Academy Award winner Angelina Jolie's kidnapped son is found alive. She realizes that the child returned to her is not her own. She faces corrupt police and a skeptical public in her relentless pursuit of answers, only to be confronted by a truth that will change her forever. Set in 1920s Los Angeles, the film also stars Academy Award nominee John Malkovich.

programme.title: Lady Psycho Killer
programme.desc: A knife-wielding killer is on the loose in a small town slicing and dicing men of questionable intent. As her brutality leaves the town littered with corpses, her bloodlust is lost on her young lover who pursues her anyway.

programme.title: Dept of F**ked Up Family Services
programme.desc: An impending visit by a social worker has Max in a tailspin; Tara horns in on Kate's friendship with Lynda; Courtney pushes Marshall to the breaking point; Neil learns Charmaine's big secret.(c)

programme.title: Explosive Diorama
programme.desc: A happy and healthy Tara prepares for an art show with Lynda, while Kate retaliates with a controversial new business; Marshall grows closer to his friend Lionel; Max makes a life-changing decision.(c)

programme.title: The Sense of an Ending
programme.desc: Tony Webster (Jim Broadbent) lives a reclusive existence in London, until he learns that a diary has been left to him by the recently deceased mother (Emily Mortimer) of an ex-girlfriend (Charlotte Rampling). As Webster investigates the diary, he is forced to face the truth about his first love and the consequences of decisions made a lifetime ago, while attempting to resolve his strained relationships with his ex-wife (Harriet Walter) and their pregnant daughter (Michelle Dockery).

programme.title: Joan Rivers: A Piece of Work
programme.desc: This insightful, hysterically funny documentary follows comedienne Joan Rivers through a year of her life while looking back on her groundbreaking, barrier-breaking career as one of the first women to make a name for herself in the tough, male-dominated world of show business.

programme.title: Whitney. "Can I Be Me"
programme.desc: Directors Nick Broomfield and Rudi Dolezal weave never before seen video, candid interviews and behind the scenes performance footage into a raw and uncensored portrait of Whitney Houston, who died suddenly at age 48 after years of struggling with addiction. Exploring her far-reaching impact, the directors focus on Houston's central dilemma: even though she had made millions of dollars and was recognized as having one of the greatest voices of all time, she still couldn't do what she wanted, either professionally or in her personal life.(c)

programme.title: Life Is Beautiful (La vita e bella)
programme.desc: Guido is a charming, bumbling Jewish waiter whose colorful imagination and playful spirit help him to woo a beautiful schoolteacher. The couple marries and has a young son, but before long, their idyllic world is threatened by Nazi soldiers who force the family into a concentration camp. Guido must now use his imagination again - this time to transform his son's tragic new surroundings into a magical wonderland.

programme.title: Changeling
programme.desc: Academy Award winner Clint Eastwood directs this drama in which Academy Award winner Angelina Jolie's kidnapped son is found alive. She realizes that the child returned to her is not her own. She faces corrupt police and a skeptical public in her relentless pursuit of answers, only to be confronted by a truth that will change her forever. Set in 1920s Los Angeles, the film also stars Academy Award nominee John Malkovich.(n)

programme.title: The Light Between Oceans
programme.desc: Lighthouse keeper Tom Sherbourne (Michael Fassbender) and spirited Isabel (Alicia Vikander) live together in married bliss on a remote, rugged island off the coast of Australia. But their windswept world is turned upside down when Isabel learns that she's unable to bear a child. One day, a drifting lifeboat washes ashore with a crying baby in it. The dilemma the couple now faces echoes far beyond the island, engulfing and irrevocably impacting their world.(n)

programme.title: Queen of the Desert
programme.desc: Gertrude Bell (Nicole Kidman) rejects the stifling rigidity of life in turn-of-the-century England, leaving it behind for a chance to travel to Tehran. She begins her lifelong adventure across the Arab world, a journey marked by danger, a passionate affair with a British officer (James Franco), and an encounter with the legendary T.E. Lawrence (Robert Pattinson).(n)

programme.title: Don't Knock Twice
programme.desc: A successful sculptor named Jess returns to the UK to rebuild her relationship with Chloe, the daughter she was forced to give up nine years ago. When she agrees to come and live with her, Jess learns that Chloe has not come to stay because she wants to get to know her mother again. She has come because she is scared that a supernatural curse has claimed the life of her boyfriend, Danny, and is now coming for her. Chloe and Danny made the mistake of visiting an abandoned house once home to a witch, that comes for you if you knock on the door.(n)

programme.title: The Sense of an Ending
programme.desc: Tony Webster (Jim Broadbent) lives a reclusive existence in London, until he learns that a diary has been left to him by the recently deceased mother (Emily Mortimer) of an ex-girlfriend (Charlotte Rampling). As Webster investigates the diary, he is forced to face the truth about his first love and the consequences of decisions made a lifetime ago, while attempting to resolve his strained relationships with his ex-wife (Harriet Walter) and their pregnant daughter (Michelle Dockery).(n)

programme.title: Bang Bang Baby
programme.desc: In this dreamy sci-fi musical set in the 1960s, an isolated small town teenager believes her hopes of becoming a famous singer will come true when her rock star idol gets stranded in town and romance blooms between them but a leak in a nearby chemical plant threatens to turn her dream into a nightmare.(n)

programme.title: Cupid's Proxy
programme.desc: Rebecca Murphy is a cynical widow whose whole world revolves around her 12 year old son, Justin - a budding musician who can't remember his late father. Rebecca has no desire to date despite efforts by her feisty neighbor, Olive, who has a love advice column called Call Me Cupid. When Olive is pressured by her editor to get with the times, she enlists Justin to help her answer a letter. Unbeknownst to Justin, she publishes his advice under the alter ego, Cupid's Proxy.(n)

programme.title: The Architect
programme.desc: Parker Posey and Eric McCormack star in this comedy about a couple who set out to build a new home and enlist the services of an uncompromising modernist architect who proceeds to build his dream house, instead of theirs.(n)

Diagnosed with spinal cancer, 27 year old Adam (Joseph Gordon-Levitt) navigates the road to recovery with the sometimes-overbearing support of his crude best friend, Kyle (Seth Rogen), his smothering mother (Anjelica Huston) and an inexperienced therapist (Anna Kendrick). Inspired by a true story, 50/50 is an honest yet hysterically funny account of a young man's journey toward healing.(n)

programme.title: Blackway
programme.desc: Revenge thriller starring Anthony Hopkins as a man haunted by the memory of his daughter's death, who comes to the aid of a young woman who is being viciously harassed by a rogue cop. Co-stars Julia Stiles and Ray Liotta.(n)

programme.title: Camp X-Ray
programme.desc: Kristen Stewart stars as a young woman who joins the military to escape her small town roots but ends up as a rookie guard at Guantanamo Bay where she strikes up an unusual and life changing friendship with one of the detainees.(n)

programme.title: Different Flowers
programme.desc: Uptight Millie Haven (Emma Bell) has always followed the rules, but when she has doubts before her big Kansas City wedding, her attitude-prone little sister Emma (Hope Lauren), comes to the rescue. They embark on a spontaneous road trip to their grandmother's farm where, with the help of Grandma Mildred (Shelley Long), they rediscover their bond. They meet a local hunk with a heart of gold, and a host of only-in-the-Midwest characters as they pick up the pieces of Millie's life.(n)

programme.title: Autumn In New York
programme.desc: A wealthy, charismatic New York restaurateur (Richard Gere) falls for a much younger hat designer (Winona Ryder) but their relationship is complicated by his philandering ways, his past connection to her family, and her debilitating illness. Jill Hennessey, Anthony LaPaglia, Sherry Stringfield and Elaine Stritch costar in this romantic melodrama.(n)

programme.title: No Love for Johnnie
programme.desc: British politics as seen through the eyes of a House of Commons member (Peter Finch), whose domestic life influences his career. Fred: Stanley Holloway. Renfrew: Donald Pleasence. Pauline: Mary Peach. Mary: Billie Whitelaw. Johnson: Paul Rogers. Alice: Rosalie Crutchley. Ralph Thomas directed.

programme.title: Girl with Green Eyes
programme.desc: A naive country girl gets a roommate with life experience when she moves into a flat in Dublin. The women meet an older writer, who is charmed by the country girl's rural ways rather than the more worldly roommate.

programme.title: Network
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about a mentally unstable news anchor who, after being told he's to be fired, becomes a media superstar when he begins delivering nightly rants and threatens an on-air suicide for his final broadcast. Paddy Chayevsky's script won an Oscar for Best Original Screenplay; Peter Firth received a posthumous Best Actor award as the unhinged newsman; and Faye Dunaway won Best Actress as a scheming network exec.

programme.title: Sunday Bloody Sunday
programme.desc: A woman has a sexual relationship with a young bisexual sculptor who also carries on an intimate relationship with a doctor who is an acquaintance of the woman. The simmering tensions between the three bubble over when the woman and the artist agree to babysit for a couple that also knows all three of the people in this romantic triangle.

programme.title: I Thank a Fool
programme.desc: An ex-doctor is charged with euthanasia in this tale of mystery and madness.

programme.title: Stranger's Return
programme.desc: King Vidor's version of Phil Stong's novel about a woman (Miriam Hopkins) returning to her Midwestern family after years in New York. Lionel Barrymore. Guy: Franchot Tone. Nettie: Irene Hervey. Simon: Stuart Erwin. Beatrice: Beulah Bondi. Allen: Grant Mitchell. Excellent cast. Strong helped with the script.

programme.title: The Richest Girl in the World
programme.desc: A rich woman swaps identities with her secretary in order to find out if she can trust a man she's about to begin dating after having been burned by fortune-hunters in the past.

programme.title: Splendor
programme.desc: A tale of a woman (Miriam Hopkins) who marries into a once-wealthy family and is ill-used by her conniving in-laws. Joel McCrea. Martin: Paul Cavanagh. Mrs. Lorrimore: Helen Westley. Clarissa: Billie Burke. Martha: Katharine Alexander. Clancey: David Niven. Elliott Nugent directed.

programme.title: Men Are Not Gods
programme.desc: Expertly acted story of extramarital love, with a theatrical background. Miriam Hopkins, Gertrude Lawrence. Tom: Rex Harrison. Katherine: Laura Smithson. Edmond: Sebastian Shaw. Producer: Val Gielgud. Skeates: A.E. Matthews. Walter Reisch directed.

programme.title: Barbary Coast
programme.desc: Melodrama of brawling San Francisco in the early gold-rush days. Directed by Howard Hawks. Edward G. Robinson, Miriam Hopkins, Joel McCrea, Walter Brennan, Frank Craven, Brian Donlevy, Clyde Cook, Harry Carey, Donald Meek, Rollo Lloyd, J.M. Kerrigan. Lots of action; fine performances. Script by Ben Hecht and Charles MacArthur.

programme.title: Virginia City
programme.desc: After escaping from a Confederate prison during the Civil War, a Union officer vows to stop a $5,000,000 gold shipment from reaching the South, but is challenged by a Southern sympathizer, whose interest in the gold is patriotic, and an outlaw, who just wants the bullion.

programme.title: The Old Maid
programme.desc: Exceptional film version of the Pulitzer Prize play about an unwed woman in the mid-19th century whose illegitimate daughter is raised as her cousin's child.

programme.title: Old Acquaintance
programme.desc: Two childhood friends both become writers, but each with a drastically different lifestyle: one remains single but becomes a critically acclaimed author, while the other gets married and writes pulp novels.

programme.title: Trouble in Paradise
programme.desc: Two sophisticated jewel thieves find themselves caught up in an unexpected love triangle when they set out to separate a Parisian widow from her fortune in gems.

programme.title: These Three
programme.desc: Lillian Hellman reworked “The Children's Hour” for this powerful story of two schoolteachers and a doctor victimized by a student's lie. Miriam Hopkins, Merle Oberon, Joel McCrea, Bonita Granville, Alma Kruger, Margaret Hamilton, Catherine Doucet. Rosalie: Marcia Mae Jones. Fine direction (William Wyler); splendid production (Samuel Goldwyn).

programme.title: The Story of Temple Drake
programme.desc: Adaptation of William Faulkner's "Sanctuary," about a reckless Southern belle and a bootlegger.

programme.title: Lady with Red Hair
programme.desc: Miriam Hopkins portrays the actress Mrs. Leslie Carter, who won theatrical fame in the 1890s with the help of producer David Belasco (Claude Rains). Mrs. Dudley: Laura Hope Crews. Payne: Richard Ainley. Bryant: John Litel. Mrs. Frazier: Helen Westley. Mrs. Brooks: Mona Barrie. Clifton: Victor Jory. Foster: Fritz Leiber. Chapman: Cecil Kellaway. Carter: Johnnie Russell. Brilliantly acted; colorful saga of the mauve era. Directed by Curtis Bernhardt.

programme.title: Wise Girl
programme.desc: An heiress (Miriam Hopkins) goes Bohemian to gain custody of her late sister's children from the father, a Greenwich Village artist (Ray Milland). Karl: Walter Abel. Fletcher: Henry Stephenson. O'Neil: Alec Craig. Mike: Guinn Williams. Mrs. Bell-Rivington: Margaret Dumont. Leigh Jason directed.

programme.title: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde
programme.desc: A kind-hearted and selfless doctor creates a serum that transforms him into a lecherous jerk. The good man attempts to win the heart of a virtuous woman, while his amoral alter-ego pursues a good-time girl.

programme.title: The Main Event
programme.desc: A Beverly Hills executive is bankrupted by her accountant, and to get back on top she must train a reluctant prizefighter with whom she has a contract, and get him back in the ring.

programme.title: What's Up, Doc?
programme.desc: Barbra Streisand and Ryan O'Neal play a mismatched couple in director Peter Bogdanovich's salute to the 1930s screwball comedies.

programme.title: The Owl and the Pussycat
programme.desc: Romance about a street-smart actress, model, and occasional prostitute who makes the acquaintance of an educated and straightlaced writer. The two end up living together, and although he is repulsed by her lifestyle and she can't stand his prudishness, their mutual attraction grows.

programme.title: Funny Girl
programme.desc: Barbra Streisand won an Oscar for her portrayal of legendary stage comedian Fanny Brice as she breaks into show business, rises to stardom with the Ziegfeld Follies and finds heartache in her marriage to big-time gambler Nicky Arnstein, who at first finds it amusing to be referred to as "Mr. Brice," but then begins to resent his wife's fame and fortune. Streisand actually shared the Best Actress Oscar that year with "The Lion in Winter" star Katharine Hepburn.

programme.title: Funny Lady
programme.desc: Barbra Streisand returns as Fanny Brice, portraying the musical comedy star's tempestuous life with her second husband, showman Billy Rose in the 1930s.

programme.title: The Way We Were
programme.desc: A tumultuous relationship between an effusive woman radical and a reticent, conservative man begins on a college campus in 1937, and struggles to remain intact throughout the coming decades. Oscars went to the title song and Marvin Hamlisch's score.

programme.title: Yentl
programme.desc: In turn-of-the-century Europe, a Jewish teenage girl disguises herself as a boy to be permitted to study the Talmud.(n)

programme.title: The Prince of Tides
programme.desc: Barbra Streisand (who also directed) portrays a Manhattan psychiatrist who gets involved with her patient's brother and tries to exorcise the demons of their dysfunctional Southern family. An adaptation of the novel by Pat Conroy (who co-adapted with Becky Johnston). (cc).(n)

programme.title: A Star Is Born
programme.desc: A fading rock star falls for a young singer who quickly eclipses him in popularity as he descends further into alcoholism and drug addiction. (repeat).(n)

programme.title: Up the Sandbox
programme.desc: Barbra Streisand offers one of her best non-musical performances as a hassled housewife who takes refuge in a fantasy world. David Selby. Elizabeth: Ariane Heller. Mrs. Yussim: Jane Hoffman. Yussim: John C. Becher. Fidel Castro: Jacobo Morales. Beineke: Paul Benedict. Keglin: George Irving. Irvin Kershner directed.(n)

programme.title: Saratoga
programme.desc: A bookie and a horse farmer's daughter fall in love as they try to gamble back funds to eradicate a debt. Jean Harlow's final movie.(n)

programme.title: It Happened One Night
programme.desc: Frank Capra's classic about a spoiled heiress on the lam from her father, and the gruff reporter who hooks up with her as they travel northward, engage in a series of misadventures and begin to fall for each other. The first film to sweep all five major Oscars: Best Picture, Director (Capra), Screenplay (Robert Riskin), Actor (Clark Gable) and Actress (Claudette Colbert).(n)

programme.title: Comrade X
programme.desc: An American reporter in the U.S.S.R. writes anti-Soviet propaganda under an assumed name and, when he is discovered, is blackmailed into helping get a hotel porter's daughter out of the country.(n)

programme.title: Band of Angels
programme.desc: A drama dealing with miscegenation in the Old South. Clark Gable, Yvonne DeCarlo, Sidney Poitier, Efrem Zimbalist Jr. Charles: Patric Knowles. Seth: Rex Reason. Canavan: Torin Thatcher. Miss Idell: Andrea King. Based on a novel by Robert Penn Warren. Directed by Raoul Walsh.(n)

programme.title: Command Decision
programme.desc: A general (Clark Gable) must send his men to certain death in bombing raids over Germany. Kane: Walter Pidgeon. Evans: Van Johnson. Garnet: Brian Donlevy. Brockhurst: Charles Bickford. Martin: John Hodiak. Malcolm: Edward Arnold. Lee: Marshall Thompson. Goldberg: Cameron Mitchell. Literate and well acted; based on the play by William Wister Haines. Directed by Sam Wood.(n)

programme.title: The King and Four Queens
programme.desc: A fugitive holes up in a ghost town with the matriarch of an outlaw quartet and the gunmen's four wives, who all make a play for him in hopes of him helping them get a share of the loot from the gang's latest stagecoach robbery.(n)

programme.title: Adventure
programme.desc: A hard-living sailor finds it rough going after marrying a librarian and trying to adapt to domestic life.(n)
Historical saga, set in 480 B.C., about a Spartan king leading 300 warriors against an overwhelming force of Persian invaders. The film is based on Frank Miller's graphic novel "300." (cc).

programme.title: Immortals
programme.desc: A brave young man named Theseus (Henry Cavill) assembles a band of fierce warriors to stop King Hyperion from acquiring a weapon that will allow him to conquer the world in this fantasy adventure based on stories from Greek mythology. (cc).

programme.title: Hawaii Five-0
programme.desc: Grover travels to Chicago to finally get a confession from his old friend Clay Maxwell about why he killed his own wife. Meanwhile, Chin and Kono accidentally stumble upon two killers who hold them at gunpoint and have no idea they are cops. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Hawaii Five-0
programme.desc: As Five-0 investigates a double homicide involving marital infidelity, McGarrett and his team recall their disastrous Valentine's Day experiences. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Hawaii Five-0
programme.desc: Danny's mother is questioned by the FBI. Meanwhile, McGarrett partners with a young man with autism who may have information that could solve the murder of the man's only friend. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Hawaii Five-0
programme.sub-title: Ka Pohaku Kihi Pa'a (The Solid Cornerstone)
programme.desc: Sang Min, Five-0's sketchy longtime confidential informant, is accused of murder, so McGarrett asks his old friend Odell Martin to defend him. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: A drunken driver kills three persons and is charged with first-degree murder in a case that causes strong disagreements between McCoy and Ross. Dressler: Daniel McDonald. Billings: David Garrison. Judge Feldman: Cliff Gorman. Susan: Kathryn Meisle. Norris: Gene Canfield. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: The lawyer for a killer whose latest victims are a social worker and a sportscaster uses exposure to TV violence as a defense. Chandler: Mitchell Lichenstein. Pressman: Dennis Boutsikaris. Thatcher: John Benjamin Hickey. Judge Samuel: Gene Saks. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: The brutal beating of a man leads to an investigation that involves two rape incidents, in one of which the victim was comatose. Harding: Erik Jensen. Greta: Cecilia Hart. Leslie: Marin Hinkle. Singer: George Bamford. Frank: Jonathan LaPaglia. Joe: George Palermo. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: The fourth season concludes as the sisters are visited by an Angel of Destiny, who offers them the chance to live normal lives in exchange for their powers as a reward for vanquishing The Source of all Evil. Meanwhile, an ambitious FBI agent spies on the sisters after discovering their names on numerous witness lists in crime reports. Phoebe: Alyssa Milano. Paige: Rose McGowan. Piper: Holly Marie Combs. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Phoebe is approached by a despondent mermaid, who struck a deal with a sea hag that requires the fabled creature to find true love or forfeit her immortality. Meanwhile, Piper's pregnancy interferes with her demon-fighting abilities as she suffers from ill-timed panic attacks. Phoebe: Alyssa Milano. Piper: Holly Marie Combs. Paige: Rose McGowan. (repeat) (cc).

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: In the conclusion of a two-part episode, Leo searches for Phoebe to return her to her natural form, and Paige tries to convince Cole to disappear from Phoebe's life.
